    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.39-41_0001a"/>
                
                <note type="authorial"><unclear>9</unclear>6 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        62, West Grove
                        Gipsyville,
                        Hull
                        Yorkshire.
                        England
                
                        14th February, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>University of Missouri,</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Columba<sic>Columbia</sic>, Missouri,</addrLine>
                                    <addrLine><hi rend="caps">U.S.A.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was with much pleasure that I have recently read one of your books ie: "Eagle Voice." When I had finished it I found that it had reawakened all my old desires to learn all that I could about this great race of people. For you see over here in Englad there is very little authentic writings on or about the Sioux Indians or for that matter, little or no information about any race of Indians at all. Though it is really the Sioux that I am deeply interested in for there is very much about their way of life and character that I admire, in fact to one such as yourself who has
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.39-41_0001b"/>
                    
                    grown so close to them and studied their way of life so much I can freely admit that spiritually, at least. I feel a great love for this people, for in their way of life I firmly believe they were very close to the spirit, as their belief in Wachon Tonka, the great Spirit, reveals. I am wondering whether you can help me to find out as much as possible about them, their customs, ceremonies, dress, languages, colour etc; so that I may identify myself with them as much as possible. My own age is twenty-nine, and my chief interest in life is to broaden and develop myself spiritually, I tell you this that you may know I write to you in all sincerity, not just to start and develop a pen-friendship. But if you are too busy to help me, then perhaps you can put me in touch with someone who can. I thank you for what consideration you may be able to show me, and remain,</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>John Young</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">39</fw>
                
            </div1>
            
            
